&lt;pre data-lang=&quot;chatlink&quot; class=&quot;language-chatlink z-code&quot;&gt;&lt;code class=&quot;language-chatlink&quot; data-lang=&quot;chatlink&quot;&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;z-source z-chatlink&quot;&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;z-punctuation z-definition z-string z-begin&quot;&gt;[&amp;amp;&lt;&#x2F;span&gt;DQIEHyQ2PT1wAKcAswAAAKkAAACvAAAAnAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAADLwAFADIAAA==&lt;span class=&quot;z-punctuation z-definition z-string z-end&quot;&gt;]&lt;&#x2F;span&gt;
&lt;&#x2F;span&gt;&lt;&#x2F;code&gt;&lt;&#x2F;pre&gt;
&lt;hr &#x2F;&gt;
&lt;div data-armory-embed=&#x27;skills&#x27; data-armory-ids=&#x27;14389,14413,14404,14410,14355&#x27;&gt;&lt;&#x2F;div&gt;&lt;div data-armory-embed=&#x27;specializations&#x27; data-armory-ids=&#x27;4,36,61&#x27; data-armory-4-traits=&#x27;1444,1449,1437&#x27; data-armory-36-traits=&#x27;1344,1315,1707&#x27; data-armory-61-traits=&#x27;2107,2095,2060&#x27;&gt;&lt;&#x2F;div&gt;
&lt;h2 id=&quot;rotation&quot;&gt;Rotation&lt;&#x2F;h2&gt;
&lt;hr &#x2F;&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The rotation for Power Spellbreaker consists of a pre-cast, and pressing 2 simple combos, &lt;span class=&quot;armory-inline&quot; data-armory-embed=&quot;skills&quot; data-armory-ids=&quot;45252&quot;&gt;&lt;&#x2F;span&gt; Breaching Strike, and &lt;span class=&quot;armory-inline&quot; data-armory-embed=&quot;skills&quot; data-armory-ids=&quot;14413&quot;&gt;&lt;&#x2F;span&gt; Dolyak Signet off cooldown.&lt;&#x2F;p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Your pre-cast skills are:&lt;&#x2F;p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Pre-cast:&lt;&#x2F;strong&gt;&lt;&#x2F;p&gt;
&lt;blockquote&gt;
&lt;ol&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;armory-inline&quot; data-armory-embed=&quot;skills&quot; data-armory-ids=&quot;14389&quot;&gt;&lt;&#x2F;span&gt; Healing Signet&lt;&#x2F;li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;armory-inline&quot; data-armory-embed=&quot;skills&quot; data-armory-ids=&quot;14355&quot;&gt;&lt;&#x2F;span&gt; Signet of Rage&lt;&#x2F;li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;armory-inline&quot; data-armory-embed=&quot;skills&quot; data-armory-ids=&quot;14413&quot;&gt;&lt;&#x2F;span&gt; Dolyak Signet&lt;&#x2F;li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;armory-inline&quot; data-armory-embed=&quot;skills&quot; data-armory-ids=&quot;14410&quot;&gt;&lt;&#x2F;span&gt; Signet of Fury&lt;&#x2F;li&gt;
&lt;&#x2F;ol&gt;
&lt;&#x2F;blockquote&gt;
&lt;p&gt;And you should always cast all 4 skills before you hit the boss. As both &lt;span class=&quot;armory-inline&quot; data-armory-embed=&quot;skills&quot; data-armory-ids=&quot;14413&quot;&gt;&lt;&#x2F;span&gt; Dolyak Signet and &lt;span class=&quot;armory-inline&quot; data-armory-embed=&quot;skills&quot; data-armory-ids=&quot;14410&quot;&gt;&lt;&#x2F;span&gt; Signet of Fury have no cast time, it should take around 2 seconds to cast all 4 skills, allowing it to be very consistently cast at the start of each fight.&lt;&#x2F;p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Listed below are the skills that you should always combo:&lt;&#x2F;p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Combo 1:&lt;&#x2F;strong&gt;&lt;&#x2F;p&gt;
&lt;blockquote&gt;
&lt;ol&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;armory-inline&quot; data-armory-embed=&quot;skills&quot; data-armory-ids=&quot;14399&quot;&gt;&lt;&#x2F;span&gt; Whirling Axe (Axe 5)&lt;&#x2F;li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;armory-inline&quot; data-armory-embed=&quot;skills&quot; data-armory-ids=&quot;14418&quot;&gt;&lt;&#x2F;span&gt; Dual Strike (Axe 4)&lt;&#x2F;li&gt;
&lt;&#x2F;ol&gt;
&lt;&#x2F;blockquote&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Combo 2:&lt;&#x2F;strong&gt;&lt;&#x2F;p&gt;
&lt;blockquote&gt;
&lt;ol&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;armory-inline&quot; data-armory-embed=&quot;skills&quot; data-armory-ids=&quot;44937&quot;&gt;&lt;&#x2F;span&gt; Disrupting Stab (Dagger 3)&lt;&#x2F;li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;armory-inline&quot; data-armory-embed=&quot;skills&quot; data-armory-ids=&quot;46233&quot;&gt;&lt;&#x2F;span&gt; Aura Slicer (Dagger 2)&lt;&#x2F;li&gt;
&lt;&#x2F;ol&gt;
&lt;&#x2F;blockquote&gt;
&lt;p&gt;And the priority you should assign for your skills and combo are:&lt;&#x2F;p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Rotation Priority:&lt;&#x2F;strong&gt;&lt;&#x2F;p&gt;
&lt;blockquote&gt;
&lt;ol&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;armory-inline&quot; data-armory-embed=&quot;skills&quot; data-armory-ids=&quot;45252&quot;&gt;&lt;&#x2F;span&gt; Breaching Strike&lt;&#x2F;li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Combo 1&lt;&#x2F;li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Combo 2&lt;&#x2F;li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;armory-inline&quot; data-armory-embed=&quot;skills&quot; data-armory-ids=&quot;14413&quot;&gt;&lt;&#x2F;span&gt; Dolyak Signet&lt;&#x2F;li&gt;
&lt;&#x2F;ol&gt;
&lt;&#x2F;blockquote&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Advanced players should note that &lt;span class=&quot;armory-inline&quot; data-armory-embed=&quot;skills&quot; data-armory-ids=&quot;14413&quot;&gt;&lt;&#x2F;span&gt; Dolyak Signet does not have a cast time, nor will it interrupt the current skill that is being casted, and can be pressed anytime as soon as it is off cooldown.&lt;&#x2F;p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;While the rotation itself is simple with few steps, do take note that both &lt;span class=&quot;armory-inline&quot; data-armory-embed=&quot;skills&quot; data-armory-ids=&quot;45252&quot;&gt;&lt;&#x2F;span&gt; Breaching Strike and &lt;span class=&quot;armory-inline&quot; data-armory-embed=&quot;skills&quot; data-armory-ids=&quot;46233&quot;&gt;&lt;&#x2F;span&gt; Aura Slicer (Dagger 2) are leap skills, and will have forced movement and animation lock when you are casting them. This may cause you to become badly positioned or hit by some mechanics as you are not able to dodge during this time.&lt;&#x2F;p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;armory-inline&quot; data-armory-embed=&quot;skills&quot; data-armory-ids=&quot;14399&quot;&gt;&lt;&#x2F;span&gt; Whirling Axe (Axe 5) also has a long channel time, and while you can move during the channel, dodging or casting another skill will end it prematurely, resulting in a loss of damage. You should thus always hold &lt;span class=&quot;armory-inline&quot; data-armory-embed=&quot;skills&quot; data-armory-ids=&quot;14418&quot;&gt;&lt;&#x2F;span&gt; Dual Strike (Axe 4) until you have finished casting &lt;span class=&quot;armory-inline&quot; data-armory-embed=&quot;skills&quot; data-armory-ids=&quot;14399&quot;&gt;&lt;&#x2F;span&gt; Whirling Axe (Axe 5), and it is better to skip &lt;span class=&quot;armory-inline&quot; data-armory-embed=&quot;skills&quot; data-armory-ids=&quot;14418&quot;&gt;&lt;&#x2F;span&gt; Dual Strike (Axe 4) altogether than to cancel &lt;span class=&quot;armory-inline&quot; data-armory-embed=&quot;skills&quot; data-armory-ids=&quot;14399&quot;&gt;&lt;&#x2F;span&gt; Whirling Axe (Axe 5).&lt;&#x2F;p&gt;
&lt;h2 id=&quot;crowd-control&quot;&gt;Crowd Control&lt;&#x2F;h2&gt;
&lt;hr &#x2F;&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You only have one CC skill in this build, &lt;span class=&quot;armory-inline&quot; data-armory-embed=&quot;skills&quot; data-armory-ids=&quot;44937&quot;&gt;&lt;&#x2F;span&gt; Disrupting Stab (Dagger 3), and as it is used as part of your damage rotation, may not be off cooldown when you need to CC.&lt;&#x2F;p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For fights requiring CC, it is recommended to swap out &lt;span class=&quot;armory-inline&quot; data-armory-embed=&quot;skills&quot; data-armory-ids=&quot;14413&quot;&gt;&lt;&#x2F;span&gt; Dolyak Signet for &lt;span class=&quot;armory-inline&quot; data-armory-embed=&quot;skills&quot; data-armory-ids=&quot;14502&quot;&gt;&lt;&#x2F;span&gt; Kick, and use &lt;span class=&quot;armory-inline&quot; data-armory-embed=&quot;skills&quot; data-armory-ids=&quot;14502&quot;&gt;&lt;&#x2F;span&gt; Kick only when you need to CC. This will result in a small DPS decrease to about ~35.0k, which is still good considering the overall simplicity of the build.&lt;&#x2F;p&gt;
&lt;h2 id=&quot;advanced-tips&quot;&gt;Advanced Tips&lt;&#x2F;h2&gt;
&lt;hr &#x2F;&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For fights with multiple phases, you should always recast your pre-cast skills at the start of each phase, ensuring that you both maximise your burst damage, as well as having enough Adrenaline to actually perform your rotation.&lt;&#x2F;p&gt;
&lt;div style=‘clear:both;’&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;&#x2F;div&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;armory-inline&quot; data-armory-embed=&quot;skills&quot; data-armory-ids=&quot;14413&quot;&gt;&lt;&#x2F;span&gt; Dolyak Signet provides an insanely high 10 stacks of stability when cast, and can be delayed to be used for skipping various fight mechanics. These 10 stacks of stability lasts 8 seconds, providing a very forgiving window between pressing &lt;span class=&quot;armory-inline&quot; data-armory-embed=&quot;skills&quot; data-armory-ids=&quot;14413&quot;&gt;&lt;&#x2F;span&gt; Dolyak Signet and the mechanic happening.&lt;&#x2F;p&gt;
&lt;div style=‘clear:both;’&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;&#x2F;div&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You can gain more DPS while having an easily accessible CC button by swapping out &lt;span class=&quot;armory-inline&quot; data-armory-embed=&quot;skills&quot; data-armory-ids=&quot;14413&quot;&gt;&lt;&#x2F;span&gt; Dolyak Signet for &lt;span class=&quot;armory-inline&quot; data-armory-embed=&quot;skills&quot; data-armory-ids=&quot;14502&quot;&gt;&lt;&#x2F;span&gt; Kick. Use &lt;span class=&quot;armory-inline&quot; data-armory-embed=&quot;skills&quot; data-armory-ids=&quot;14502&quot;&gt;&lt;&#x2F;span&gt; Kick off cooldown, inserting it to the bottom of your priority list, while maintaining at least 1 stack of &lt;span class=&quot;armory-inline&quot; data-armory-embed=&quot;skills&quot; data-armory-ids=&quot;14502&quot;&gt;&lt;&#x2F;span&gt; Kick for any CC bars. You can also only use 1 stack of &lt;span class=&quot;armory-inline&quot; data-armory-embed=&quot;skills&quot; data-armory-ids=&quot;14502&quot;&gt;&lt;&#x2F;span&gt; Kick, saving 2 stacks for more CC, and it will still be a DPS increase over &lt;span class=&quot;armory-inline&quot; data-armory-embed=&quot;skills&quot; data-armory-ids=&quot;14413&quot;&gt;&lt;&#x2F;span&gt; Dolyak Signet.&lt;&#x2F;p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This can be done for all fights, but is highly recommended for fights with many phases and requiring high CC.&lt;&#x2F;p&gt;
